        "action": "Fund review of access & use of Naltrexone for alcohol dependence & chronic pain ",
        "additional_details": "We think wider access could help save lives and public money\u2014act now to remove barriers.\r\nWe think low-dose naltrexone can help manage chronic pain and addiction, offering a safer, non-opioid option. Alcohol and drug misuse cost the UK over \u00a332 billion annually. Drug treatment yields \u00a34\u2013\u00a321 return per \u00a31 spent. Expanding access could save NHS and social care budgets. Fair access is a public health and economic priority.",
        "background": "We want Government to fund a review into wider access to low-dose Naltrexone for Alcohol Dependence and as a treatment for chronic pain. Studies have shown it\u2019s cost-effective, NICE-approved for alcohol dependency, and it could help reduce NHS strain. ",
